---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy - Track Your Labs"
  description="Learn how Track Your Labs protects your privacy and handles your personal information."
>
  <main class="flex-1 px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-10 pb-6 md:pb-8 lg:pb-10 pt-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full">
    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-full break-words">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      
      <p class="text-sm italic mb-6">Last updated: April 23, 2025</p>
      
      <p class="break-words">
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Snowflake Health, LLC</strong> ("Snowflake Health," "we," "our," or "us") collects, uses, discloses, and protects your personal information when you visit <strong>trackyourlabs.com</strong> (the "Site") or use our products and services, including our lipid-panel subscription plans, AI health-assistant, mobile apps, and customer-support channels (collectively, the "Services").
      </p>
      
      <p class="break-words mt-3">
        We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying with applicable laws such as the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 ("HIPAA"), the California Consumer Privacy Act and its amendment ("CCPA/CPRA"), and the EU General Data Protection Regulation ("GDPR"), where they apply.
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-3 md:p-4 rounded-md my-6">
        <p class="font-bold">Key points in plain language</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
          <li>We collect only the data needed to run our Services.</li>
          <li>We never sell your personal information.</li>
          <li>Health-related data is encrypted and stored in HIPAA-compliant systems.</li>
          <li>You control your data and can request deletion at any time.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
      
      <div class="overflow-x-auto -mx-4 md:mx-0">
        <div class="min-w-full inline-block align-middle">
          <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300 text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Category</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[150px]">Examples</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Source</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Account Information</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Name, email, password, phone number</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">You create or update an account</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Payment Information</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Card number (tokenized), billing address, transaction totals</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Our payment processor (Stripe) when you subscribe</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Health & Lab Data</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Lipid-panel results, test dates, lab location, critical-result flag</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Labcorp, Quest, Junction Connect, or at-home kit providers</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">AI Coach Chat History</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Conversation transcripts, AI recommendations, timestamps</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Automatically captured while you use the AI Health Assistant</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Self-Reported Data</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Dietary preferences, lifestyle habits, manual logs</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">You voluntarily provide via the dashboard or apps</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Device & Usage Data</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">IP address, browser type, device ID, pages viewed, referring URL</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Automatically collected via cookies and similar tech</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Support Interactions</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Call recordings, emails, ticket notes</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">You interact with our support team or Lindy AI agent</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-2">Sensitive Data</h3>
      <p class="break-words">
        Data related to your laboratory results, AI-coach chat history, and health status is considered <strong>Protected Health Information (PHI)</strong> under HIPAA and <strong>Special Category Data</strong> under GDPR. We handle it with heightened safeguards (see Section 5).
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p class="break-words">We use personal information to:</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Provide the Services</strong> – create your account, schedule lab orders, deliver results, and power the AI coach.</li>
        <li><strong>Improve and personalize</strong> – train AI models (with de-identified data), analyze usage to enhance features.</li>
        <li><strong>Process payments</strong> – manage subscriptions, refunds, and fraud prevention.</li>
        <li><strong>Communicate with you</strong> – service emails, reminders, updates, marketing (with your opt-in).</li>
        <li><strong>Comply with legal obligations</strong> – HIPAA, state laws, bookkeeping.</li>
        <li><strong>Protect rights and safety</strong> – investigate misuse, enforce terms, detect security incidents.</li>
      </ol>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        We do <strong>not</strong> use your PHI for targeted advertising.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">3. Legal Bases for Processing (GDPR/UK GDPR)</h2>
      <p class="break-words">If you are in the European Economic Area or United Kingdom, our legal bases are:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Contract</strong> – processing necessary to perform our contract with you (core Services).</li>
        <li><strong>Consent</strong> – marketing emails, connecting third-party apps, or processing special-category data you voluntarily supply.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> – accounting, HIPAA compliance.</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> – fraud prevention, product improvement (balanced against your privacy rights).</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        You may withdraw consent at any time (see Section 8).
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">4. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p class="break-words">We share data only as described below:</p>
      
      <div class="overflow-x-auto -mx-4 md:mx-0 mt-4">
        <div class="min-w-full inline-block align-middle">
          <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300 text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Recipient</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[150px]">Purpose</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Safeguards</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Laboratory partners</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Fulfill your test orders and return results</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">HIPAA business-associate agreements (BAAs)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Lab Test Ordering partners</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Physician authorization of lab orders</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">HIPAA BAA</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Payment processor</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Secure payment processing</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">PCI-DSS compliance</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Cloud hosting & analytics</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Infrastructure, usage insights</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Data-processing addenda, encryption</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Service providers</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Operational communications</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Confidentiality clauses</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Legal or regulatory authorities</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Compliance with law, court orders</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">We disclose only the minimum required</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Successor entity</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Merger, acquisition, or asset sale</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Continuity of privacy commitments</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell or rent your personal information.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">5. Data Security</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> TLS 1.3 in transit; AES-256 at rest.</li>
        <li><strong>Access controls:</strong> role-based, MFA, least privilege.</li>
        <li><strong>Regular audits:</strong> HIPAA and SOC-2 aligned.</li>
        <li><strong>Incident response:</strong> 24/7 monitoring; we notify affected users and regulators as required by law.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>PHI & lab data (including AI chat transcripts that reference health information):</strong> retained for <strong>7 years</strong> in accordance with HIPAA record-keeping rules.</li>
        <li><strong>General AI chat history not tied to PHI:</strong> retained for up to <strong>3 years</strong> to improve user experience and let you reference past conversations. You can delete individual chats in your dashboard at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>Account data:</strong> kept while your account is active and for up to <strong>2 years</strong> after closure for fraud prevention and bookkeeping.</li>
        <li><strong>AI training data:</strong> de-identified and aggregated; retained indefinitely.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        You may request earlier deletion where permitted (see Section 8).
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">7. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p class="break-words">We use:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> – account login, payment checkout.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> – measure traffic (Google Analytics, privacy-friendly IP truncation).</li>
        <li><strong>Preference cookies</strong> – remember language or dark-mode settings.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        You can manage cookies in your browser settings or opt-out of analytics via our Cookie Banner.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="break-words">Depending on where you live, you may have rights to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Access</strong> – know what data we hold.</li>
        <li><strong>Portability</strong> – receive a copy in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong> – update inaccurate data.</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion</strong> – request we erase certain data.</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction/Objection</strong> – limit or stop specific processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-out of marketing</strong> – unsubscribe at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        Submit requests by emailing <strong>privacy@trackyourlabs.com</strong> or via Dashboard → Settings → Privacy. We will verify your identity and respond within statutory timelines.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-2">CCPA/CPRA Disclosures (California Residents)</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li>We have disclosed Identifiers, Commercial Information, Internet Activity, and Health Data for business purposes (see Section 4).</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not sell</strong> or share your data for cross-context behavioral advertising.</li>
        <li>You may exercise your "Right to Know," "Delete," or "Correct" as described above.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-2">HIPAA Access & Amendment</h3>
      <p class="break-words">
        You may obtain copies of your PHI or request amendments under 45 CFR §164.524-526 by contacting us at the address below.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p class="break-words">
        Our Services are <strong>not directed to children under 13</strong>. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such data, contact us for deletion.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">10. International Transfers</h2>
      <p class="break-words">
        Your information may be processed in the United States. We rely on Standard Contractual Clauses or other approved mechanisms for transfers from the EEA/UK.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p class="break-words">
        We may update this Privacy Policy. We will post the revised version and change the "Last updated" date. Material changes will be emailed or otherwise prominently communicated at least 30 days before they take effect.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="break-words">If you have questions or concerns, please contact:</p>
      
      <blockquote class="bg-gray-100 p-3 md:p-4 rounded-md my-4 border-l-4 border-gray-400">
        <p class="font-bold">Privacy Officer</p>
        <p>Snowflake Health, LLC</p>
        <p class="break-all"><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@trackyourlabs.com</p>
      </blockquote>
      
      <p class="break-words">
        You may also lodge a complaint with your local data-protection authority or the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services Office for Civil Rights.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }
  
  .prose table {
    width: 100%;
  }
  
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>